"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-news-world-1928977-france-Paris-olympics-opening-ceremony-paris-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  The people of France have hailed their 2024 Olympic Games opening ceremony, with one person even claiming it was better than London 2012.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 16, \"end\": 22, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9589106562848335, \"rank\": 0.04118355363575747, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 127, \"end\": 138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999997185525841, \"rank\": 2.796022296338827e-07, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony in Paris has sparked a lot of debate due to its unconventional style.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 223, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 157, \"end\": 162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999788542, \"rank\": 2.1220699527993558e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the scenes that caused the most reaction was arecreation of 'The Last Supper' by Leonardo Da Vinciusing drag queens, dancers, and other performers.\", \"from\": 225, \"to\": 378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 312, \"end\": 320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9964111086501865e-14, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Viewers were also left confused by a performer Philippe Katerine who played the Greek God of wine, festivity and theatre, Dionysus.\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 427, \"end\": 444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philippe Katerine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\"}, {\"begin\": 460, \"end\": 465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.7131607385810517, \"rank\": 0.3912745648620182, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}, {\"begin\": 502, \"end\": 510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6139750647690344e-16, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony received mixed reviewsfrom the international audience, but the French seemed over the moon with the display.\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 589, \"end\": 595, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9897435093953649, \"rank\": 0.01031659710666371, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"People branded French actor Katerine, who was painted blue and appeared almost naked, a \\\"national treasure\\\" and were overjoyed to see him introduced on the international stage, with some branding it the result of \\\"French genius\\\".\", \"from\": 636, \"to\": 865, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 651, \"end\": 657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9897435093953649, \"rank\": 0.01031659710666371, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 850, \"end\": 856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9897435093953649, \"rank\": 0.01031659710666371, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One wrote: \\\"One billion human beings who discover Philippe Katerine in this way, that's my France.\\\"\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 965, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 916, \"end\": 933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philippe Katerine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\"}, {\"begin\": 957, \"end\": 963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9589106562848335, \"rank\": 0.04118355363575747, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"READ MORE:Paris Olympics opening ceremony video deleted from YouTube after outrage    One social media user, Tim Marks, said: \\\"I am sticking to my guns, last night's #OpeningCeremony was way better than London 2012, you lads really messed that up, and if I was British I'd feel ashamed and somewhat inferior....\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 1278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 977, \"end\": 991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1028, \"end\": 1035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"score\": 0.9999998826945171, \"rank\": 1.1730551871495988e-07, \"text\": \"YouTube\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\"}, {\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999997185525841, \"rank\": 2.796022296338827e-07, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So you know I feel sorry for you guys.\\\"\", \"from\": 1279, \"to\": 1318, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Marie Le Conte, a French journalist based in the UK, said: \\\"God I am feeling patriotic, we are just so unapologetically weird.\\\"\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1329, \"end\": 1334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Count\", \"score\": 0.8925605569401724, \"rank\": 0.1203717960107407, \"text\": \"Conte\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Count\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Count\"}, {\"begin\": 1338, \"end\": 1344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9897435093953649, \"rank\": 0.01031659710666371, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1369, \"end\": 1371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999674502571189, \"rank\": 3.188623968592182e-05, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Christophe Rehage said: \\\"I am proud of France for being so bold and unapologetically weird, and it rocks that they had a metal band play at the opening ceremony.\\\"\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1488, \"end\": 1494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9589106562848335, \"rank\": 0.04118355363575747, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Matt Currey also posted: \\\"Just can not define the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1680, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hints of genius, madness, beauty, failure, boredom, brilliance, surprise and much more.\", \"from\": 1681, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe it's very Paris and very 2024.\\\"\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1806, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1785, \"end\": 1790, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999788542, \"rank\": 2.1220699527993558e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, another X user said: \\\"The ceremony was the next level of art.\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 1880, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Proud to be French!\\\"\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1901, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you.\", \"from\": 1903, \"to\": 2012, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding.\", \"from\": 2013, \"to\": 2089, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time.\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2122, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy Policy    The performer who starred as Dionysus defended the ceremony after criticism grew.\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2178, \"end\": 2186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6139750647690344e-16, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said: It would not be fun if there were no controversy.\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2290, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Would not it be boring if everyone agreed on this planet?\\\"\", \"from\": 2291, \"to\": 2349, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The New York Times branded the ceremony a \\\"bloated made-for-TV spectacle\\\" while the New York Post said it was \\\"boring, ill-conceived and choppy.\\\"\", \"from\": 2351, \"to\": 2496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2351, \"end\": 2369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7439436582866344e-21, \"text\": \"The New York Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_New_York_Times\"}, {\"begin\": 2435, \"end\": 2448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_Post\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"New York Post\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_Post\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_Post\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French newspaper Le Figaro added that the show was \\\"great but some of it was just too much.\\\"\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2498, \"end\": 2504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9897435093953649, \"rank\": 0.01031659710666371, \"text\": \"French\"